files in this folder need to open in SPSS;
"opinion and vote change.sav" and "opinion and vote convert.sav" are data extracted from simulations' raw data;
"correlation.spv" is test result for continuous variables through  Pearson method;
"crosstabs.spv" is test result for discrete variables through contingency tables.
Note 1: abs_name is the absolute value of the raw data; this transformation considered symmetry of the raw data
Note 2: variable named "stability of the issue" is the variable defined in the paper as "conservative degree".
